```c
if (prev && prev->func && ZEND_USER_CODE(prev->func->common.type)) {
    ...
} else {
    zend_execute_data *prev_call = prev;
    while (prev_call) {
        ...
        prev = prev_call->prev_execute_data;
        if (prev && prev->func && ZEND_USER_CODE(prev->func->common.type)) {
            ZVAL_STR_COPY(&tmp, prev->func->op_array.filename);
            _zend_hash_append_ex(stack_frame, ZSTR_KNOWN(ZEND_STR_FILE), &tmp, 1);
            ZVAL_LONG(&tmp, prev->opline->lineno);
            _zend_hash_append_ex(stack_frame, ZSTR_KNOWN(ZEND_STR_LINE), &tmp, 1);
            break;
        }
        prev_call = prev;
    }
    filename = NULL;
}
```
Here, too, `prev->opline` and `prev->func->op_array.filename` are dereferenced without checking if `prev->opline` is NULL (or that `prev->func->type == ZEND_USER_FUNCTION`).  
This can also cause null dereference/segfaults.

**Full patch should also add `prev->opline` NULL-check in this secondary context.**

