responded: The root cause of the segfault is that `prev->opline` can be NULL, but the code dereferences it unconditionally at:
```c
if (prev->opline->opcode == ZEND_HANDLE_EXCEPTION) {
    ...
} else {
    lineno = prev->opline->lineno;
}
```
If `prev->opline` is NULL, this will cause a segmentation fault. The correct fix is to check if `prev->opline` is non-NULL before dereferencing it, and provide a fallback value for `lineno` if it is NULL (e.g., use `prev->func->op_array.line_end` or 0).

